      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should I lock in a 1-year or 5-year GIC?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "This depends on the yield curve and your cash needs. When rates are high but expected to fall, a 5-year GIC locks in the high rate. However, a 1-year GIC provides more flexibility. Many people use a GIC ladder to blend the benefits of both."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];

